    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "the problem is those studies feel very academic. in the real world, my margins are razor thin. it feels like the policy is being driven more by social justice motives than by actual economic reality for people in rural areas. do you think it's possible that these policies are fundamentally biased against small, independent businesses in favor of larger corporations that can actually afford to absorb the cost?",
